In a phone call between President Obama and Prime Minister Erdogan of Turkey, they discussed the situation in Syria and Egypt. They expressed concern about the presence of foreign extremists in Syria and agreed on the importance of supporting a unified Syrian opposition. They also expressed concern about the situation in Egypt and their commitment to promoting a democratic and inclusive way forward. The two leaders agreed to continue coordinating closely on shared interests. President Obama also wished the Prime Minister and the Turkish people a happy Ramazan holiday.